Whatever be the meaning of that mystical dipping into the unseen world of soul, the sense of personal contact and comfort which by psychic law is the inevitable result of absorbed prayer, it is evident that per- sonal experience can supply no criterion of opinion.

The whole question resolves itself into this—Is our standard the real mind and heart of Christ, or some conception of him removed from reality, perhaps as far removed from it as was the expected Messiah for whose kingdom the Pharisees compassed sea and land in missionary zeal.
